Painted and decorated this number on the last day of 2022. Swipe for finish piece ♥️ Sorry for the lack of updates and post, its been a wild and crazy ride. 

In 2022, I felt that i have reached a point in time when i feel i can no longer grow my career and its been really stagnant. Nothing excites me (that much) anymore and designs and orders are just it. I wanted to do more teaching, designing and business development. So i did a YOLO travel to europe with my mum for a month and re-thought my future business directions and personal plans. 

But with a grateful heart, q3 and q4 was really exciting. We moved to a charming shophouse in jln besar. I went overseas to teach. Built a strong team tht made over 4000 pieces of chocolate, more than 450 cookies and amazingly over 600 cakes and wedding cakes in the final quater of 2022. 

I am certainly looking forward to a major change of jobscope in 2023 for myself and taking on more challenging and exciting projects. 

Clear eyes, strong heart, can’t lose ♥️

A major throw back to this custom dessert we made for @vancleefarpels 2 years ago. It is suppose to celebrate the launch of their perlee collection. 🧐

Honestly one of the most challenging projects ever, to make sure that the glaze is light and even. 🥸 The most challenging part? Clean up. 😂

Jokes aside these mousse cakes are super! Black forest, ispahan and the exotic, missing it already!

What are your 2023 goals? For me, i want to become a better version of myself, have more time for myself outside of work, create more beautiful pieces, teach more and of course expand yume with more exciting projects.

Will you be my Valentines? 🤍

Exactly one more week to go, the thing about being born on Valentines and in the service industry is that everywhere is always fully booked and orders are peak so I guess I celebrate as I pipe your cakes haha!

Our Valentines orders are closing soon, ladies & gentlemen if you haven’t make your plans this is the final call so don’t miss it!
 
Happy season of love everyone ♥️

Everyone have 24 hours a day.
8 hours for sleeping
8 hours for working
3 hours for meals
2 hours to get ready and commute 
.
We are left with 3 hours to do what we love daily if we are lucky. 
.
Some try to improve themselves, some try to work on their mental state, some exercise to have better health. 
.
I say, why not spend the 8 hours working doing what you love and you will never have to work a day in your life again. 
.
We hope you love our work as much as we love ours.

I can still remember i did my first royal icing cookie order for the makeup brand ZA, more than 10 years ago. I couldn’t understand why my cookie refuse to dry - even after 3 days. And all the online tutorials dident even make sense at all, the colors were patchy and dull. I managed to complete the order but i develop a special hate for royal icing cookie there after. 🥲 10 years later, with professional experience and understanding towards this medium. I found love again. And i want to share my love for this challenging medium with you. 🥰

Launching our newest Royal Icing masterclass inspired from Alice in the Wonderland. Sign up link in profile. 

Class Date: 24 June 2023
Time: 10am-5.30pm
.

2023 is a curious year. With multiple wake up calls and reality checks. Despite the challenges and feeling lonely, i have the opportunity to meet amazing people who touched my life, in the best way possible. 
.
Together, we realised that everyone is, more often then not, trying to figure out the best for ourselves. And since we only live once, there is no way we can go back in time to fix mistakes. Only forward looking and gentle nudges towards a better path. Its okay to figure things out. Its okay to be not in a good place all the time. Its okay to take a break. 
.
Most importantly, “just keep swimming”.

Romantic blushes, soft ivories, all edible sugar flower, a timeless keepsake.
.
Do you know that sugar and wafer paper flowers can last a lifetime if kept properly in the right conditions?
The mood for this picture is on point. 🥸

Some close up details of this cake that i did years back. Waferpaper hydrangea, hand cut and made petal by petal. The amount of work is insane, because i wanted different color in the same petal. HAHAHAHA.
.
So what is the most insane thing you did for your cake?
New design drop! Special client requested a remix from out old design, adding edible sakura to the whole theme.

As someone who markets mainly on social media for, i know painfully little people and i describe myself as “living under a rock”. One of the things i really dislike is when someone tells me about how someone else is doing, how successful they are, and probably their new campaigns. Whist i can be happy for the people i have not met, i find it distracting for many of reasons. 
.
The person which i am competing at the end of the day is myself. It does not matter what other people is doing because we need to focus on our inner voice and not the noise outside before we can be successful in our own ways. 
.
Here’s a muted longevity peach cake for you out there who should learn to love yourself more and listen to yourself more. 🍑

From design to execution, our cakes are not done by one person. A team of amazing souls are behind your cake even when they are not in this ig story ♥️ timelapse make making this cake too easy! Please send us abit of love this way if this story inspire you in anyway.

For those of you who wanted to admire our cake slowly, here’s a still shot! Probably the 2nd biggest cake we made so far. But definitely the most stunning. 
.
More than 400 edible flowers and foliage on the cake. And i am more then blessed to have the opportunity to design and bring this dream into reality. 100% thankful for the cake’s amazing backdrop! 
.

Here’s a old photo of me in 2019, winning the NEO startup award from Singapore Spirit of Enterprise, nominated by the students of SIT. I am definitely shocked to realise the last time i introduced myself was August 2022 and this photo from pre-covid times were never posted. 
.
I am Amber, the chef owner of @yumepatisserie and here’s some fun facts about me:

1. I am a awfully private person who is trying to be more “seen” in socia media but facing tremendous challenges.

2. I don’t have a favourite color! I think as a designer having a favourite color will be a potential pitfall since it will limit your views. 

3. Cliche as it sounds, my favourite fruit to be made into dessert is Apples (and sometimes lemon)! Apple crumble, caramel apple tarte tatin, apple tart, green apple yuzu cake (my own creation!), apple strudel, apple cider.

Designed in 2021, till this date i still hold it close to my heart because its modern, minimalist and a pain in the ass to make 😂
.
My client asked me why did i stop posting photos of all my cakes. And the truth is, after looking back at the design and execution 1-2 years later, sometimes i am less proud of my work. Because as i improve, i can see how to make the originial better. 😝
.
Mental note to self - love myself more and be proud of my works more.
